snippet.textDisplay: They basically had a glorified break dance sparring exhibition. They both came into the fight with the gameplan to wait for the other guy to commit first then look to counter strike. As soon as Yoel caught him with that overhand left in the 1st round, Izzy went into Jon Jones mode the rest of the fight. All that tough talk about him being the first guy to "stop him properly" went out the window after that. He obviously landed the leg kick effectively in the 3rd and 4th round but he really didn't do shit in the first two rounds and was looking scary in the last round when Yoel finally got in his face. Everytime Yoel got close, Izzy got on his bike. He literally ran a lap half way around the cage at one point trying to get away from Yoel. Go watch it again. I didn't see Yoel run away one time. This isn't boxing. The cage is too big and you can't make someone fight you in this sport especially if they obviously don't want to engage. I had a lot of respect for Izzy before this fight because he talked the talk and backed up in every fight. HE'S the one that said he was going to bring the fight the Yoel and beat him like no one else but when it came down to back it up this time, he fought scared af. He did not compete like a true champion this fight. Then he tried to convince himself that he was the one pushing the pace and he did what he had to do to win the fight. GTFOH This is #1 bullshit. Yoel definitely should have walked him down after he saw Izzy didn't want the smoke. The judges gave the fight to the "Champ" because he's the money fighter just like they did with Jon Jones when he fought against Reyes. We all know how the politics work in the fight game. Both guys lost the fight to me.

Israel did what a good corner would tell him to do given what was put in front of him and did a good job even though it would and did make it a boring fight. At the end of the day it's about winning first and foremost and Israel did what he had to to get the win.
